reviews.review_text: I always come to this place, closer to my home and kids love Mcdonalds ,always buy and go , sometimes s dine in, today we choose dine in , we are not really satisfied with this store before ,until we met the manager Michelle (i am not sure ,but i think she is the manager,  i hope so ),she is very patient with kids and nice to me  ,she told me she loves kids ,she is very kind ,I am so glad and lucky to met her  , kids also very happy too ,  ,thank you , Kid-friendliness: Manager very kind to kids

Arguably one of the better operated McDonalds! Foods come out hot, quick turnover that means, and well trained staffs! Its our go to in the morning before church on Sunday and course kids love happy meals. However franchise should focus on fair pricing as a fast food rather than returning capital to investors, and growing margin profile YoY.  Once it becomes higher price than a regular food, it wont last. Chicken Mcmuffin was an interesting one! Mcflurry is so addictive. Hah! Guess you have the rights to enforce those prices.

I can only remember experiences of using the drive through in this location, my review is based on that. Its  MacDonald food, its no avocado toast, but it is needed on certain  occasions. The staff are cheerful and friendly. One late night crew member helped me out of a bit of bind on my last visit. I owe you one Sir. One caution; It is tight around the drive through windows Simon Parking: There are plenty of parking spaces, and across the street is the Lansdowne Center with a huge parking lot of its own.

Was the best macdonald Ive been to in awhile way better then the 2 on marine dr. Everything was perfect and fast, friendly staff everyone smiling put extra napkins etc more then normal and Mac chicken sauce in the bag without asking which is appreciated
We were attended by Mishell and she gave us excellent service. She took our order in a very impressive way. She made our day very good.
Summer deals on frappes, iced coffee, and soda (pop). Delicious food and drinks. The donuts were super yummy as well.

Cashier was patient to customer asking if certain products will return. Attentive staff cleaning all the tables and the seats in the back, i could hear him wiping one spot with effort and taking care of my messy tray tonight. Good work everyone in night shift.

The dine in is very nice .The staff are very friendly. I ordered my food they gave me number to be seated and in no time my food was delivered on table .the server ask if we need anything .I say 5 star service Kid-friendliness: They have Ballon stand

The manager here the girl on nights is the best and most friendliest manager. The kitchen staff is super friendly. Ive had such a good experience This is the best mcdonalds Ive ever been too! Thank you so much  for letting me use your wifi.
I cant say thank you enough. I walked a while just for a drink. Lucky I didnt have to wait too long  .

One of the better McDonalds forsure. Quick wait times in the drive thru, foods always Hott and fresh, friendly staff, milk shake machine is usually is working here, Ill usually stop in here on my way to work in the mornings

Classic McDonalds, with a classic drive thru. The actual McDs parking is small, but directly attached to a larger strip mall which has tonnes of parking abd super easy to walk over. If youre looking for some fries or any McDs classic, this is a solid place to come.

First time here just grabbing a customized drink and apple pies. Can hear the manager emphasized our customization until the other employee acknowledged it. Just saw the reviews now.. wow. Hopefully they are addressing those issues
They follow Mc Donalds standard, but there is a noticeable difference. They hire excellent kids. In my opinion, the counter attendants are more friendly in this Mc Donalds.

This is by far the best McDonalds in all of Richmond so I am told by many of the guests that come through my door. We all ways have the best staff ready to greet anyone who graces our doors, food is always warm and fresh, and tables are always clean and there it was a place to sit. We take pride at 2 and Blundell in keeping our guest and neighbours very comfortable at the busiest of times well still not compromising on the best service at the window or drive through.

5/5. The staff here are so, so kind and helpful. Especially considering with what they have to deal with..I was there the other day in the drive thru and the patron infront of me decided it was OK to smoke their cigarette, to literally hold it in the same hand that theyre taking the food with from the drive thru attendant. That is DISGUSTING...there are signs that say no smoking/vaping. Theres also basic human decency and common sense that dictate that you dont force your disgusting habit on others....but common sense is seriously lacking these days, as I think we can all agree. Ive also seen people throw their trash down out their window because the attendant wont throw it away for them. Its a drive thru for McDonalds, not an express garbage drop off. Get it together people. Anyways, shout out to Andrea especially, youre doing a great job. Keep it up!!!!
McDonalds employee Vandean Nguyen provided me with excellent service at this location. He portrayed a brilliant personallity.

This is an amazing place. Its cozy, the service is absolutely great as well. I love the touchscreen order things, the food usually comes within 5 minutes so you dont have to wait long (though the drive is best for those in an extreme rush).

Average service and food. Nothing noteworthy. Had a good experience! Well located to grab a few McDoubles before heading off to watch a play. Late night service means dropping by for a snack is easy any time of day.
Everything is good, only the service is too slow,they need more worker to work. Every customer talking about the slow service for waiting order.

edit: changing my review from 2 to 5 stars i don t know if they changed their management or what but this McDonald s has really turned it around in the last month of so! they consistently get my order correct, fill my drink to the brim, and actually don t put salt in my fries when I ask them not to. thank you so much for bringing so much improvement and love to my local McDs!! i m so grateful and will remain loyal to Blundell!! keep on being amazing!! old review below: man, i want to like this place bc it s in my neighbourhood, but they keep getting my drive thru orders wrong! this is frustrating bc i only find out their error when i am too far away to redeem the order. ex. giving me grilled chicken instead of crispy chicken in my wrap, an absolute disappointment ensued 5km away from the establishment. i suggest you visit the granville location instead, they take wayyy more pride in their franchise.

Excellent. Specially the girl named harwrinder was fabulous . She deals with customer very nicely. I had an issue with order and first time i saw a McDonald s employee solve the issue with such concern
Very delicious. Typical McDonald s
Very good service. There coffee is always so fresh and customer service is fantastic. Special thanks to Simran. You are the best
Fantastic. New decor.  My favorite break place for the last 27 years.  The girl who used to be a cashier got promoted; glad to see good employee got recognized.  Cant beat Mr. Macdonald.
Fantastic customer service by the gal name  Balpreet . Wonderful experience even at 2:30 am. She deserves a good promotion please.
